Display Types

Test 1 of 213 - 01-1-display-types
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Display Types - Display Types</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #1a1a2e;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-family: "DejaVu Sans";
        }
        .section {
            background-color: #16213e;
            border: 2px solid #0f3460;
            padding: 15px;
        }
        .section-title {
            color: #e94560;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .block-demo {
            display: block;
            background-color: #0f3460;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .inline-demo {
            display: inline;
            background-color: #e94560;
            padding: 2px 8px;
        }
        .inline-block-demo {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #4a6fa5;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 5px;
            width: 100px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">Display Types</div>
        <div class="block-demo">Block 1</div>
        <div class="block-demo">Block 2</div>
        <div>
            <span class="inline-demo">Inline 1</span>
            <span class="inline-demo">Inline 2</span>
            <span class="inline-demo">Inline 3</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="inline-block-demo">IB 1</div>
            <div class="inline-block-demo">IB 2</div>
            <div class="inline-block-demo">IB 3</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Flexbox Direction - Flexbox - Direction and Gap</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #1a1a2e;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-family: "DejaVu Sans";
        }
        .section {
            background-color: #16213e;
            border: 2px solid #0f3460;
            padding: 15px;
        }
        .section-title {
            color: #e94560;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .flex-row {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: row;
            gap: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .flex-column {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 5px;
        }
        .flex-item {
            background-color: #4a6fa5;
            padding: 8px 12px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">Flexbox - Direction and Gap</div>
        <div class="flex-row">
            <div class="flex-item">Row 1</div>
            <div class="flex-item">Row 2</div>
            <div class="flex-item">Row 3</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-row">
            <div class="flex-column">
                <div class="flex-item">Col 1</div>
                <div class="flex-item">Col 2</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-column">
                <div class="flex-item">Col A</div>
                <div class="flex-item">Col B</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Flex Shorthand</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #1a1a2e;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: "DejaVu Sans";
        }
        .section {
            background-color: #16213e;
            border: 2px solid #0f3460;
            padding: 15px;
        }
        .section-title {
            color: #e94560;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .subsection {
            background-color: #1e3a5f;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        .subsection-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        .container {
            display: flex;
            gap: 5px;
            margin: 8px 0;
            background-color: #0f3460;
            padding: 5px;
        }
        .box {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            background-color: #e94560;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .label {
            color: #aaa;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">CSS flex Shorthand Property</div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: none (0 0 auto)</div>
            <div class="label">Items don't grow or shrink</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: none;">A</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: none;">B</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: none;">C</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: auto (1 1 auto)</div>
            <div class="label">Items grow and shrink equally</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: auto;">A</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: auto;">B</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: auto;">C</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: initial (0 1 auto)</div>
            <div class="label">Items can shrink but don't grow</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: initial;">A</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: initial;">B</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: initial;">C</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: 1 (single number)</div>
            <div class="label">flex: 1 = grow:1, shrink:1, basis:0</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1;">1</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 2;">2</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1;">1</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: grow shrink (two numbers)</div>
            <div class="label">flex: 1 0 = grow:1, shrink:0</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1 0;">1 0</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 2 0;">2 0</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1 0;">1 0</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">flex: grow shrink basis (three values)</div>
            <div class="label">flex: 1 0 100px = grow:1, shrink:0, basis:100px</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1 0 100px;">100px</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 2 0 50px;">50px</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1 0 100px;">100px</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Mixed flex values</div>
            <div class="label">Combining different flex values</div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="box" style="flex: none;">none</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 1;">1</div>
                <div class="box" style="flex: 2;">2</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">CSS text-indent Property</div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Pixel values:</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 0 (default):</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 0;">This paragraph has no text indent. The first line starts at the normal position, flush with the left margin.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 20px:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 20px;">This paragraph has a 20 pixel text indent. Notice how only the first line is indented, while subsequent lines start at the normal position.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 40px:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 40px;">This paragraph has a 40 pixel text indent. The indentation is more pronounced, creating a traditional book-style paragraph opening.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 60px:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 60px;">This paragraph has a 60 pixel text indent. Large indents can be useful for creating visual hierarchy or special formatting effects.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Em values (relative to font-size):</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 1em:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 1em;">This paragraph has a 1em text indent. One em is equal to the current font size, so the indent scales with the text.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 2em:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 2em;">This paragraph has a 2em text indent. Two ems creates a larger indent that still scales proportionally with font size.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 3em (larger font):</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 3em; font-size: 18px;">This paragraph has a 3em indent with larger font. Notice how the indent is proportionally larger because of the bigger font size.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Negative values (hanging indent):</div>
            <div class="example" style="padding-left: 50px;">
                <div class="label">text-indent: -30px (with padding-left: 50px):</div>
                <p style="text-indent: -30px;">This creates a hanging indent effect. The first line extends to the left of subsequent lines. Useful for bibliographies and lists.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Percentage values:</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">text-indent: 10%:</div>
                <p style="text-indent: 10%;">This paragraph has a 10% text indent based on the containing block's width. Percentage indents scale with container width.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Multiple paragraphs:</div>
            <div class="example" style="text-indent: 30px;">
                <div class="label">Container with text-indent: 30px (inherited):</div>
                <p>First paragraph inherits the text indent from the container. Only the first line of each paragraph is indented.</p>
                <p>Second paragraph also inherits the text indent. Each paragraph starts with an indented first line.</p>
                <p>Third paragraph continues the pattern. Text indent makes multi-paragraph text more readable.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">CSS line-height Property</div>

        <!-- Normal (default) -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Normal (default ~1.2):</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: normal:</div>
                <p style="line-height: normal;">This paragraph uses the normal line height, which is typically around 1.2 times the font size. This is the browser's default and provides comfortable reading spacing between lines of text.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Unitless numbers -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Unitless number (multiplier):</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 1.0 (tight):</div>
                <p style="line-height: 1.0;">This paragraph has a line height of 1.0, meaning the line height equals the font size exactly. Lines are very close together, which can make text harder to read but saves vertical space.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 1.5:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 1.5;">This paragraph has a line height of 1.5, meaning 1.5 times the font size. This provides more generous spacing between lines and is often recommended for body text readability.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 2.0 (double-spaced):</div>
                <p style="line-height: 2.0;">This paragraph has a line height of 2.0, creating double-spaced text. This is often used in academic documents or when extra space between lines is desired for annotations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pixel values -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Pixel values (absolute):</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 16px (same as font-size):</div>
                <p style="line-height: 16px;">This paragraph has a 16px line height with 16px font. Lines are tightly packed together since line height equals font size. Pixel values are absolute and don't scale with font size.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 24px:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 24px;">This paragraph has a 24px line height. With a 16px font size, this creates 1.5x spacing. Pixel values give precise control but don't adapt to font size changes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 32px:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 32px;">This paragraph has a 32px line height. With a 16px font size, this creates 2x spacing. Notice how subsequent lines have significant gaps between them.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Em values -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Em values (relative to font-size):</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 1em:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 1em;">This paragraph has a 1em line height. One em equals the current font size, so this is equivalent to line-height: 1.0. Lines are tightly packed together.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 1.5em:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 1.5em;">This paragraph has a 1.5em line height. This provides comfortable spacing that scales with the font size. Em units are useful for responsive typography.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 2em with larger font:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 2em; font-size: 18px;">This paragraph has a 2em line height with 18px font. The actual line height is 36px (18 * 2). Notice how larger fonts with em-based line heights create proportionally larger spacing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Percentage values -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Percentage values:</div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 100%:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 100%;">This paragraph has a 100% line height, equivalent to 1.0 or 1em. The line height equals the font size exactly. Percentage is relative to the element's font size.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 150%:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 150%;">This paragraph has a 150% line height. This is equivalent to 1.5 or 1.5em. Percentage values are often used for their clarity in expressing the relationship to font size.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
                <div class="label">line-height: 200%:</div>
                <p style="line-height: 200%;">This paragraph has a 200% line height, creating double-spaced text. This is equivalent to line-height: 2.0 or line-height: 2em.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Comparison -->
        <div class="subsection">
            <div class="subsection-title">Side-by-side comparison:</div>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px;">
                <div class="example" style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="label">line-height: 1.0</div>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.0; font-size: 14px;">Tight spacing. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="example" style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="label">line-height: 1.5</div>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; font-size: 14px;">Normal spacing. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="example" style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="label">line-height: 2.0</div>
                    <p style="line-height: 2.0; font-size: 14px;">Wide spacing. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: "DejaVu Sans";
        }
        .section {
            background-color: #16213e;
            border: 2px solid #0f3460;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .section-title {
            color: #e94560;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .label {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 11px;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .row {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .box {
            background-color: #2a2a4a;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #444;
        }
        .ellipsis {
            width: 200px;
            overflow: hidden;
            white-space: nowrap;
            text-overflow: ellipsis;
        }
        .clip {
            width: 200px;
            overflow: hidden;
            white-space: nowrap;
            text-overflow: clip;
        }
        .normal {
            width: 200px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">Text Overflow Comparison</div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="label">text-overflow: ellipsis (200px width)</div>
            <div class="box ellipsis">This is a long text that will be truncated with ellipsis</div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="label">text-overflow: clip (200px width)</div>
            <div class="box clip">This is a long text that will be clipped without ellipsis</div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="label">No overflow restriction (200px width, wraps)</div>
            <div class="box normal">This is a long text that will wrap to multiple lines normally</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Sizing & Object Fit Test</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            background: #1a2744;
            color: white;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #ff6b9d;
            margin: 20px 0 10px 0;
            font-size: 18px;
        }
        .section {
            background: #0f3460;
            border: 2px solid #16537e;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .demo-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .demo-container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 5px;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 11px;
            color: #aaa;
        }
        .box {
            background: #4fc3f7;
            border: 2px solid #0288d1;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: #1a2744;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 14px;
        }

        /* Aspect ratio boxes */
        .aspect-16-9 {
            aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
            width: 160px;
        }
        .aspect-4-3 {
            aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
            width: 120px;
        }
        .aspect-1-1 {
            aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
            width: 80px;
        }
        .aspect-9-16 {
            aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
            width: 60px;
        }

        /* Overflow test boxes */
        .overflow-box {
            width: 100px;
            height: 60px;
            background: #4fc3f7;
            border: 2px solid #0288d1;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #1a2744;
        }
        .overflow-x-hidden {
            overflow-x: hidden;
            overflow-y: visible;
        }
        .overflow-y-hidden {
            overflow-x: visible;
            overflow-y: hidden;
        }
        .overflow-x-scroll {
            overflow-x: scroll;
            overflow-y: hidden;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Aspect Ratio Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2>aspect-ratio</h2>
        <div class="demo-row">
            <div class="demo-container">

            </div>
            <div class="demo-container">
                <span class="label">4:3 (120px wide)</span>

        /* Pie chart effect */

            );
            border-radius: 50%;

                hsl(0, 100%, 50%),

                hsl(180, 100%, 50%),
                hsl(240, 100%, 50%),
                hsl(300, 100%, 50%),
                hsl(360, 100%, 50%)
            );

Quote

Test 108 of 213 - 59-1-quote
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS ::before/::after Pseudo-elements</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #e74c3c;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .section {
            background: #2d3e50;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        }

        /* Basic ::before example */
        .quote::before {
            content: '"';
            color: #3498db;
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .quote::after {
            content: '"';
            color: #3498db;
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Icon-style before */
        .note::before {
            content: "Note: ";
            color: #f39c12;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Bullet point style */
        .bullet::before {
            content: "* ";
            color: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* Arrow indicator */
        .arrow::after {
            content: " ->";
            color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Label with background */
        .labeled::before {
            content: "NEW";
            background-color: #e74c3c;
            color: white;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-right: 8px;
        }

        /* Required field marker */
        .required::after {
            content: " *";
            color: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* Currency prefix */
        .price::before {
            content: "$";
            color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* attr() function */
        .attr-demo::after {
            content: attr(data-suffix);
            color: #9b59b6;
            font-style: italic;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>::before and ::after Pseudo-elements</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="quote">To be or not to be</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

Test 116 of 213 - 60-1-centered
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS margin: auto Centering</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #e74c3c;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .section {
            background: #2d3e50;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        }

        .label {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        /* Centered box with fixed width */
        .centered {
            width: 200px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            background: #3498db;
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Right-aligned with margin-left: auto */
        .right-aligned {
            width: 150px;
            margin-left: auto;
            background: #27ae60;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Left-aligned (margin-right: auto only) */
        .left-aligned {
            width: 150px;
            margin-right: auto;
            background: #9b59b6;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Multiple centered boxes */
        .small-centered {
            width: 100px;
            margin: 10px auto;
            background: #e74c3c;
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Narrow centered container */
        .narrow-container {
            width: 300px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: #34495e;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        .inner-centered {
            width: 150px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: #f39c12;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #000;
        }

        /* No width = no centering (should be full width) */
        .no-width {
            margin: 10px auto;
            background: #1abc9c;
            padding: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>margin: auto Centering</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Centered (margin: 0 auto)</div>
        <div class="centered">Centered Box</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

Input Types

Test 122 of 213 - 61-1-input-types
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Attribute Selectors</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #e74c3c;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .section {
            background: #2d3e50;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        }

        .label {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        input, button {
            display: block;
            margin: 8px 0;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border: 1px solid #555;
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
        }

        /* [attr] - attribute exists */
        [disabled] {
            opacity: 0.5;
            background: #444;
        }

        /* [attr=value] - exact match */
        [type="text"] {
            border-color: #3498db;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        [type="password"] {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        [type="email"] {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        /* [attr^=value] - starts with */
        [class^="btn"] {
            background: #9b59b6;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
        }

        /* [attr$=value] - ends with */
        [class$="primary"] {
            background: #3498db;
        }

        [class$="danger"] {
            background: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* [attr*=value] - contains */
        [data-info*="special"] {
            border: 2px dashed #f39c12;
        }

        /* [attr~=value] - word match */
        [data-tags~="featured"] {
            background: #27ae60;
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 10px;
        }

        /* [attr|=value] - dash match (for lang codes) */
        [lang|="en"] {
            font-style: italic;
        }

        /* Combining attribute selectors */
        input[type="text"][required] {
            border-left: 4px solid #e74c3c;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Attribute Selectors</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">[type="..."] - Input types</div>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Text input (blue border)">
        <input type="password" placeholder="Password (red border)">
        <input type="email" placeholder="Email (green border)">
    </div>
</body>
</html>

HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Attribute Selectors</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #e74c3c;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .section {
            background: #2d3e50;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        }

        .label {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        input, button {
            display: block;
            margin: 8px 0;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border: 1px solid #555;
            background: #1e2a38;
            color: #e0e0e0;
        }

        /* [attr] - attribute exists */
        [disabled] {
            opacity: 0.5;
            background: #444;
        }

        /* [attr=value] - exact match */
        [type="text"] {
            border-color: #3498db;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        [type="password"] {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        [type="email"] {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            border-width: 2px;
        }

        /* [attr^=value] - starts with */
        [class^="btn"] {
            background: #9b59b6;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
        }

        /* [attr$=value] - ends with */
        [class$="primary"] {
            background: #3498db;
        }

        [class$="danger"] {
            background: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* [attr*=value] - contains */
        [data-info*="special"] {
            border: 2px dashed #f39c12;
        }

        /* [attr~=value] - word match */
        [data-tags~="featured"] {
            background: #27ae60;
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 10px;
        }

        /* [attr|=value] - dash match (for lang codes) */
        [lang|="en"] {
            font-style: italic;
        }

        /* Combining attribute selectors */
        input[type="text"][required] {
            border-left: 4px solid #e74c3c;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Attribute Selectors</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">[disabled] - Disabled state</div>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Normal input">
        <input type="text" placeholder="Disabled input" disabled>
        <button disabled>Disabled Button</button>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

            background: white;

        h3 {
            margin: 20px 0 10px;
            font-size: 16px;

        .container {

            margin-bottom: 15px;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        /* :not() selector tests */
        .not-test div {
            padding: 8px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            background: #e0e0e0;
        }
        .not-test div:not(.special) {
            background: #90EE90;
        }
        .not-test .special {
            background: #FFB6C1;
        }
    </style>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>61 - Advanced Selectors - Adjacent Sibling Selector (+)</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
        }
        h3 {
            margin: 20px 0 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        /* Adjacent sibling selector (+) tests */
        .adjacent-test h4 {
            margin: 5px 0;
            color: #333;
        }
        .adjacent-test h4 + p {
            color: blue;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }
        .adjacent-test p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            color: #666;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h3>Adjacent Sibling Selector (+)</h3>
    <div class="container adjacent-test">
        <h4>Heading 1</h4>
        <p>This paragraph immediately follows h4 (blue, bold)</p>
        <p>This paragraph does not (gray)</p>
        <h4>Heading 2</h4>
        <p>This also immediately follows h4 (blue, bold)</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

            font-size: 14px;

            background: white;
        }
        h3 {
            margin: 20px 0 10px;

            display: inline-block;
            padding: 5px 10px;

            background: #ddd;

        .general-test .marker ~ span {
            background: #87CEEB;
        }
    </style>

        <span>Also after (blue)</span>

            width: calc(300px / 2);
            background: #F0E68C;
        }
        .calc-test .box6 {

            background: #98FB98;
        }
    </style>

        .brightness-150 { background: #3498db; filter: brightness(1.5); }

        /* Contrast filter */
        .contrast-50 { background: #888; filter: contrast(0.5); }
        .contrast-100 { background: #888; filter: contrast(1); }
        .contrast-200 { background: #888; filter: contrast(2); }

        /* Grayscale filter */
        .grayscale-0 { background: #e74c3c; }
        .grayscale-50 { background: #e74c3c; filter: grayscale(50%); }
        .grayscale-100 { background: #e74c3c; filter: grayscale(100%); }

        /* Sepia filter */
        .sepia-0 { background: #3498db; }
        .sepia-50 { background: #3498db; filter: sepia(0.5); }
        .sepia-100 { background: #3498db; filter: sepia(1); }

        /* Saturate filter */
        .saturate-0 { background: #2ecc71; filter: saturate(0); }
        .saturate-100 { background: #2ecc71; filter: saturate(1); }
        .saturate-200 { background: #2ecc71; filter: saturate(2); }

        /* Invert filter */
        .invert-0 { background: #333; color: white; }
        .invert-50 { background: #333; color: white; filter: invert(0.5); }
        .invert-100 { background: #333; color: white; filter: invert(1); }

        .combined1 { background: #3498db; filter: grayscale(1) brightness(1.2); }

    <style>
        body {

            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
        }
        h3 {
            margin: 20px 0 10px;

            height: 80px;

            color: white;

            border-radius: 8px;
            text-align: center;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        /* Background color transition */
        .bg-transition {
            background-color: #3498db;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .bg-transition:hover {
            background-color: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* Color transition */
        .color-transition {
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: #ecf0f1;
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .color-transition:hover {
            color: #f1c40f;
        }

        /* Opacity transition */
        .opacity-transition {
            background-color: #9b59b6;
            opacity: 1;
            transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
        }
        .opacity-transition:hover {
            opacity: 0.5;
        }

        /* Border color transition */
        .border-transition {
            background-color: #1abc9c;
            border: 4px solid #16a085;
            transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .border-transition:hover {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
        }

        /* Multiple transitions */
        .multi-transition {
            background-color: #e67e22;
            color: white;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .multi-transition:hover {
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: #f1c40f;
        }

        .timing-row {
            display: flex;

        }

            background-color: #e74c3c;
        }
        .timing-linear {
            transition: background-color 0.5s linear;
        }
        .timing-ease {
            transition: background-color 0.5s ease;
        }
        .timing-ease-in {
            transition: background-color 0.5s ease-in;
        }
        .timing-ease-out {
            transition: background-color 0.5s ease-out;
        }
        .timing-ease-in-out {
            transition: background-color 0.5s ease-in-out;
        }

        /* Different durations */

        /* Drop shadow examples */

        }
        .shadow-large {
            filter: drop-shadow(8px 8px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4));
        }
        .shadow-colored {
            background: #e74c3c;
            filter: drop-shadow(5px 5px 8px rgba(231, 76, 60, 0.6));
        }

            filter: drop-shadow(5px 5px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5));

            background: #9b59b6;
        }

        .shadow-with-grayscale {
            filter: drop-shadow(4px 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)) grayscale(1);
        }
        .shadow-with-brightness {
            filter: drop-shadow(4px 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4)) brightness(1.2);
        }

        }
        .blur-12 {
            filter: drop-shadow(4px 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5));
        }
        .blur-20 {

        }

            width: 80px;
            height: 80px;
            border-radius: 50%;

        }
        .rounded {
            border-radius: 20px;
            filter: drop-shadow(3px 3px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5));
        }
        .square {
            border-radius: 0;
            filter: drop-shadow(3px 3px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5));
        }

        /* Card-like shadow */
        .card {
            width: 150px;
            height: 100px;
            background: white;
            color: #333;
            border-radius: 8px;
            filter: drop-shadow(0px 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15));
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
    </style>

HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>70 - CSS Animations</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
        }
        h3 {
            margin: 20px 0 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .demo-section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }
        .box-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 30px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            align-items: center;
        }

        /* Basic box style */
        .box {
            width: 80px;
            height: 80px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: white;
            font-size: 10px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            text-align: center;
            background: #3498db;
        }

        /* Pulse animation - background color */
        @keyframes pulse {
            0% { background-color: #3498db; }
            50% { background-color: #e74c3c; }
            100% { background-color: #3498db; }
        }
        .pulse {
            animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
        }

        /* Fade animation - opacity */
        @keyframes fade {
            0% { opacity: 1; }
            50% { opacity: 0.3; }
            100% { opacity: 1; }
        }
        .fade {
            animation: fade 1.5s ease infinite;
        }

        /* Color shift animation */
        @keyframes colorShift {
            0% { background-color: #9b59b6; color: white; }
            33% { background-color: #f1c40f; color: #333; }
            66% { background-color: #2ecc71; color: white; }
            100% { background-color: #9b59b6; color: white; }
        }
        .color-shift {
            animation: colorShift 3s linear infinite;
        }

        /* Border color animation */
        @keyframes borderPulse {
            0% { border-color: #3498db; }
            50% { border-color: #e74c3c; }
            100% { border-color: #3498db; }
        }
        .border-pulse {
            border: 4px solid #3498db;
            animation: borderPulse 1s ease infinite;
        }

        /* Different durations */
        .fast {
            animation: pulse 0.5s ease infinite;
        }
        .normal {
            animation: pulse 1s ease infinite;
        }
        .slow {
            animation: pulse 3s ease infinite;
        }

        /* Different timing functions */
        .linear-timing {
            animation: pulse 2s linear infinite;
        }
        .ease-in-timing {
            animation: pulse 2s ease-in infinite;
        }
        .ease-out-timing {
            animation: pulse 2s ease-out infinite;
        }
        .ease-in-out-timing {
            animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
        }

        /* Alternate direction */
        @keyframes slideColor {
            from { background-color: #3498db; }
            to { background-color: #e74c3c; }
        }
        .alternate {
            animation: slideColor 1s ease alternate infinite;
        }
        .reverse {
            animation: slideColor 1s ease reverse infinite;
        }
        .alternate-reverse {
            animation: slideColor 1s ease alternate-reverse infinite;
        }

        /* Animation with delay */
        .delayed {
            animation: pulse 2s ease 1s infinite;
        }

        /* Finite iterations */
        .three-times {
            animation: pulse 1s ease 3;
        }

        /* Fill mode forwards */
        @keyframes toRed {
            from { background-color: #3498db; }
            to { background-color: #e74c3c; }
        }
        .fill-forwards {
            animation: toRed 2s ease forwards;
        }

        /* Paused animation */
        .paused {
            animation: pulse 1s ease infinite;
            animation-play-state: paused;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h3>CSS Animations (@keyframes)</h3>
    <p>Testing CSS animations with various configurations. Animations are visible in interactive mode.</p>

    <h3>Basic Animations</h3>
    <div class="demo-section">
        <div class="box-row">
            <div class="box pulse">Pulse</div>
            <div class="box fade">Fade</div>
            <div class="box color-shift">Color<br>Shift</div>
            <div class="box border-pulse">Border<br>Pulse</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Different Durations</h3>
    <div class="demo-section">
        <div class="box-row">
            <div class="box fast">0.5s</div>
            <div class="box normal">1s</div>
            <div class="box slow">3s</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Timing Functions</h3>
    <div class="demo-section">
        <div class="box-row">
            <div class="box linear-timing">linear</div>
            <div class="box ease-in-timing">ease-in</div>
            <div class="box ease-out-timing">ease-out</div>
            <div class="box ease-in-out-timing">ease-in-out</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Animation Direction</h3>
    <div class="demo-section">
        <div class="box-row">
            <div class="box alternate">alternate</div>
            <div class="box reverse">reverse</div>
            <div class="box alternate-reverse">alternate<br>reverse</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Special Cases</h3>
    <div class="demo-section">
        <div class="box-row">
            <div class="box delayed">1s delay</div>
            <div class="box three-times">3 times</div>
            <div class="box fill-forwards">forwards</div>
            <div class="box paused">paused</div>
        </div>
    </div>

            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 14px;

            float: left;
            width: 80px;

            margin: 5px;

            color: white;

            float: right;
            width: 80px;
            height: 60px;
            background: #2196F3;
            margin: 5px;
            padding: 5px;
            color: white;
        }

        /* Clear styles */
        .clear-left { clear: left; }
        .clear-right { clear: right; }
        .clear-both { clear: both; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h3>1. Basic Float Left</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left">Float Left</div>
    This text should wrap around the floated element. The float takes up space on the left side.
</div>

<h3>2. Basic Float Right</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-right">Float Right</div>
    This text should wrap around the floated element. The float takes up space on the right side.
</div>

<h3>3. Both Float Left and Right</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left">Left</div>
    <div class="float-right">Right</div>
    Text flows between the two floats, wrapping around both sides.
</div>

<h3>4. Multiple Left Floats (Stack)</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left" style="width:60px;height:40px;">L1</div>
    <div class="float-left" style="width:60px;height:40px;">L2</div>
    <div class="float-left" style="width:60px;height:40px;">L3</div>
    Multiple same-direction floats should stack horizontally.
</div>

<h3>5. Clear Left</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left" style="height:40px;">Float L</div>
    <div class="float-right" style="height:80px;">Float R</div>
    <div class="clear-left" style="background:#ffcdd2;padding:5px;">Clear Left - below left float only</div>
</div>

<h3>6. Clear Right</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left" style="height:80px;">Float L</div>
    <div class="float-right" style="height:40px;">Float R</div>
    <div class="clear-right" style="background:#ffcdd2;padding:5px;">Clear Right - below right float only</div>
</div>

<h3>7. Clear Both</h3>
<div class="container">
    <div class="float-left" style="height:50px;">Float L</div>
    <div class="float-right" style="height:70px;">Float R</div>
    <div class="clear-both" style="background:#c8e6c9;padding:5px;">Clear Both - below all floats</div>
</div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="label">word-wrap: break-word</div>
            <div class="box" style="word-wrap: break-word;">
                Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious is a very long word.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    </div>

Is Basic

Test 169 of 213 - 76-1-is-basic
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:is() and :where() Selectors Test</title>
<style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 10px 0 5px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        .box {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            background: #ecf0f1;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 11px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        /* Test 1: :is() basic matching */
        :is(.red, .danger) {
            color: #e74c3c;
        }

        :is(.blue, .info) {
            color: #3498db;
        }

        :is(.green, .success) {
            color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Test 2: :where() basic matching (same as :is but zero specificity) */
        :where(.purple, .special) {
            color: #9b59b6;
        }

        /* Test 3: :is() with type selectors */
        :is(h3, h4) {
            color: #e67e22;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        /* Test 4: Combining :is() with other selectors */
        .parent :is(.child1, .child2) {
            background: #f39c12;
            color: white;
        }

        /* Test 5: Multiple classes in :is() */
        :is(.highlight, .important, .featured) {
            border: 3px solid #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Test 6: :where() specificity test - this should be overridden */
        :where(.override-test) {
            color: gray;
            background: lightgray;
        }
        /* This class selector (specificity 0,1,0) should override :where (specificity 0,0,0) */
        .override-test {
            color: #2ecc71;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        /* Test 7: :is() specificity - uses highest specificity of arguments */
        :is(#high-spec, .low-spec) {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">1. :is() Basic Matching</div>
<div class="container">
    <p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 12px; color: #666;">:is(.red, .danger) matches either class</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="box red">class="red"</div>
        <div class="box danger">class="danger"</div>
        <div class="box blue">class="blue"</div>
        <div class="box info">class="info"</div>
        <div class="box green">class="green"</div>
        <div class="box success">class="success"</div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

Focus Vs Focus Visible Input

Test 176 of 213 - 77-1-focus-vs-focus-visible-input
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:focus-visible Test - :focus vs :focus-visible on Input</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 1: Basic :focus-visible styling */
        .test-input {
            padding: 8px 12px;
            font-size: 14px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            border-radius: 4px;
            outline: none;
        }

        /* :focus applies to all focus (mouse and keyboard) */
        .test-input:focus {
            border-color: #3498db;
        }

        /* :focus-visible only applies to keyboard focus */
        .test-input:focus-visible {
            outline: 3px solid #e74c3c;
            outline-offset: 2px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">1. :focus vs :focus-visible on Input</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>Click (mouse) = blue border only. Tab (keyboard) = blue border + red outline.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="label">Text input:</div>

Focus Style Comparison

HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:focus-visible Test - Focus Style Comparison</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 4: Custom focus styles comparison */
        .custom-focus {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #95a5a6;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        /* Only :focus - always visible */
        .focus-only:focus {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        /* Only :focus-visible - keyboard only */
        .focus-visible-only:focus-visible {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            background: #f5eef8;
        }

        /* Both - different styles for mouse vs keyboard */
        .focus-both:focus {
            border-color: #f39c12;
        }
        .focus-both:focus-visible {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            outline: 2px dashed #e74c3c;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">4. Focus Style Comparison</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>Compare different focus style strategies:</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div>
            <div class="label">:focus only (green)</div>
            <input type="text" class="custom-focus focus-only" placeholder="Always shows">
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="label">:focus-visible only (purple)</div>
            <input type="text" class="custom-focus focus-visible-only" placeholder="Keyboard only">
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="label">Both (orange/red)</div>
            <input type="text" class="custom-focus focus-both" placeholder="Different styles">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>

Focus Vs Focus Within Comparison

Test 185 of 213 - 78-5-focus-vs-focus-within-comparison
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:focus-within Test - :focus vs :focus-within Comparison</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 5: Compare :focus vs :focus-within */
        .comparison-box {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        /* :focus - only matches when the element itself is focused */
        .focus-test:focus {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        /* :focus-within - matches when element or descendant is focused */
        .focus-within-test:focus-within {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            background: #f5eef8;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">5. :focus vs :focus-within Comparison</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>Compare: :focus only matches the focused element; :focus-within matches ancestors too.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div>
            <div class="label">:focus (green) - div can't receive focus</div>
            <div class="comparison-box focus-test">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Focus me">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="label">:focus-within (purple)</div>
            <div class="comparison-box focus-within-test">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Focus me">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

Has Element Types

Test 187 of 213 - 79-1-has-element-types
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:has() Selector Test</title>
<style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 1: Basic :has() - parent with specific child */
        .card {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 150px;
        }

        /* Card with image gets special styling */
        .card:has(img) {
            border-color: #3498db;
            background: #ebf5fb;
        }

        /* Card with .important class child */
        .card:has(.important) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .card img {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background: #3498db;
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .important {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Test 2: :has() with type selectors */
        .list-item {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        /* List item containing a link */
        .list-item:has(a) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
            border-left: 3px solid #3498db;
        }

        /* List item containing strong text */
        .list-item:has(strong) {
            background: #fff8e6;
            border-left: 3px solid #f39c12;
        }

        /* Test 3: :has() with multiple selectors */
        .box {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #95a5a6;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 120px;
        }

        /* Box with either input OR button */
        .box:has(input, button) {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            background: #f5eef8;
        }

        .box input, .box button {
            padding: 8px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            display: block;
        }

        /* Test 4: Nested :has() */
        .outer {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 3px solid #bdc3c7;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .inner {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        /* Outer has inner with .active */
        .outer:has(.inner.active) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .inner.active {
            border-color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Test 5: :has() with class selectors */
        .status-box {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        .status-box:has(.success) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .status-box:has(.error) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .status-box:has(.warning) {
            border-color: #f39c12;
            background: #fef9e7;
        }

        .success { color: #27ae60; }
        .error { color: #e74c3c; }
        .warning { color: #f39c12; }

        /* Test 6: Specificity comparison */
        .spec-test {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        /* :has() specificity = highest specificity of its arguments */
        /* :has(.foo) = (0, 1, 0) like a class */
        .spec-test:has(.foo) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
        }

        /* :has(#bar) = (1, 0, 0) like an ID - should win */
        .spec-test:has(#bar) {
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">1. :has() with Element Types</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>Cards containing specific elements get styled differently.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="label">Plain card</div>
            <span>No special children</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <img>
            <div class="label">Card with image</div>
            <span>Blue border</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="label">Card with important</div>
            <span class="important">Important content!</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

        .section {

            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 1: Basic :has() - parent with specific child */
        .card {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 150px;
        }

        /* Card with image gets special styling */
        .card:has(img) {
            border-color: #3498db;
            background: #ebf5fb;
        }

        /* Card with .important class child */
        .card:has(.important) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .card img {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background: #3498db;
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .important {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Test 2: :has() with type selectors */
        .list-item {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        /* List item containing a link */
        .list-item:has(a) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
            border-left: 3px solid #3498db;
        }

        /* List item containing strong text */
        .list-item:has(strong) {
            background: #fff8e6;
            border-left: 3px solid #f39c12;
        }

        /* Test 3: :has() with multiple selectors */
        .box {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #95a5a6;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 120px;
        }

        /* Box with either input OR button */
        .box:has(input, button) {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            background: #f5eef8;
        }

        .box input, .box button {
            padding: 8px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            display: block;
        }

        /* Test 4: Nested :has() */
        .outer {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 3px solid #bdc3c7;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .inner {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        /* Outer has inner with .active */
        .outer:has(.inner.active) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .inner.active {
            border-color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Test 5: :has() with class selectors */
        .status-box {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        .status-box:has(.success) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .status-box:has(.error) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .status-box:has(.warning) {
            border-color: #f39c12;
            background: #fef9e7;
        }

        .success { color: #27ae60; }
        .error { color: #e74c3c; }
        .warning { color: #f39c12; }

        /* Test 6: Specificity comparison */
        .spec-test {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        /* :has() specificity = highest specificity of its arguments */
        /* :has(.foo) = (0, 1, 0) like a class */
        .spec-test:has(.foo) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
        }

        /* :has(#bar) = (1, 0, 0) like an ID - should win */
        .spec-test:has(#bar) {
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">2. :has() with Type Selectors</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>List items styled based on their contents.</p>
    <div class="list-item">Plain text item</div>
    <div class="list-item">Item with <a href="#">a link</a></div>
    <div class="list-item">Item with <strong>bold text</strong></div>
    <div class="list-item">Just another plain item</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

        /* :has(#bar) = (1, 0, 0) like an ID - should win */
        .spec-test:has(#bar) {
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">6. :has() Specificity</div>
<div class="container">
    <p>:has() specificity = highest specificity argument. ID (#bar) beats class (.foo).</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="spec-test">
            <span class="foo">Has .foo only (blue)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-test">
            <span id="bar">Has #bar only (red)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-test">
            <span class="foo" id="bar">Has both - #bar wins (red)</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>:has() Selector Test</title>
<style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .section {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            margin: 15px 0 8px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Test 1: Basic :has() - parent with specific child */
        .card {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #bdc3c7;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 150px;
        }

        /* Card with image gets special styling */
        .card:has(img) {
            border-color: #3498db;
            background: #ebf5fb;
        }

        /* Card with .important class child */
        .card:has(.important) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .card img {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background: #3498db;
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .important {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Test 2: :has() with type selectors */
        .list-item {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        /* List item containing a link */
        .list-item:has(a) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
            border-left: 3px solid #3498db;
        }

        /* List item containing strong text */
        .list-item:has(strong) {
            background: #fff8e6;
            border-left: 3px solid #f39c12;
        }

        /* Test 3: :has() with multiple selectors */
        .box {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #95a5a6;
            margin: 10px;
            min-width: 120px;
        }

        /* Box with either input OR button */
        .box:has(input, button) {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            background: #f5eef8;
        }

        .box input, .box button {
            padding: 8px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            display: block;
        }

        /* Test 4: Nested :has() */
        .outer {
            padding: 15px;
            border: 3px solid #bdc3c7;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .inner {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        /* Outer has inner with .active */
        .outer:has(.inner.active) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .inner.active {
            border-color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Test 5: :has() with class selectors */
        .status-box {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        .status-box:has(.success) {
            border-color: #27ae60;
            background: #d5f5e3;
        }

        .status-box:has(.error) {
            border-color: #e74c3c;
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }

        .status-box:has(.warning) {
            border-color: #f39c12;
            background: #fef9e7;
        }

        .success { color: #27ae60; }
        .error { color: #e74c3c; }
        .warning { color: #f39c12; }

        /* Test 6: Specificity comparison */
        .spec-test {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            margin: 5px;
        }

        /* :has() specificity = highest specificity of its arguments */
        /* :has(.foo) = (0, 1, 0) like a class */
        .spec-test:has(.foo) {
            background: #e8f6ff;
        }

        /* :has(#bar) = (1, 0, 0) like an ID - should win */
        .spec-test:has(#bar) {
            background: #fdf2f2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="section">7. How :has() Works</div>
<div class="container">
    <p><strong>The :has() selector:</strong></p>
    <p>1. Matches an element if ANY of its descendants match the argument selector(s)</p>
    <p>2. Multiple selectors can be comma-separated: :has(img, video)</p>
    <p>3. Specificity = highest specificity of its arguments</p>
    <p>4. Similar to :focus-within but works with any selector, not just focus state</p>
</div>

</body>
</html>

        .grid-rows .item {
            background: #ce93d8;

            text-align: center;

Grid Placement

Test 197 of 213 - ng-195-grid-placement
Chrome Reference
Hokuto Output
HTML/CSS Source Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>CSS Grid Placement</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: #1a1a2e;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 0;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #ff6b9d;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .label {
            font-size: 11px;
            color: #888;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        /* Grid with explicit placement */
        .grid-placement {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 80px);
            grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 60px);
            gap: 5px;
        }
        .grid-placement .item {
            background: #4fc3f7;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #1a1a2e;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
        .grid-placement .span-col {
            grid-column: 1 / 3;
            background: #ff6b9d;
        }
        .grid-placement .span-row {
            grid-row: 2 / 4;
            background: #81c784;
        }
        .grid-placement .span-both {
            grid-column: 3 / 5;
            grid-row: 2 / 4;
            background: #ffb74d;
        }

        /* Grid with span keyword */
        .grid-span {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 100px);
            grid-template-rows: repeat(2, 70px);
            gap: 10px;
        }
        .grid-span .item {
            background: #ce93d8;
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #1a1a2e;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .grid-span .wide {
            grid-column: span 2;
            background: #4db6ac;
        }
        .grid-span .tall {
            grid-row: span 2;
            background: #ef5350;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>CSS Grid Placement</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Explicit grid lines (grid-column: 1/3, grid-row: 2/4)</div>
        <div class="grid-placement">
            <div class="item span-col">col 1-3</div>
            <div class="item">3</div>
            <div class="item">4</div>
            <div class="item span-row">row 2-4</div>
            <div class="item span-both">col 3-5<br>row 2-4</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Span keyword (grid-column: span 2)</div>
        <div class="grid-span">
            <div class="item wide">span 2 cols</div>
            <div class="item">2</div>
            <div class="item tall">span 2 rows</div>
            <div class="item">4</div>
            <div class="item">5</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

        }

        /* minmax with fr - flexible columns with minimum */
        .grid-minmax-fr {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: minmax(100px, 1fr) minmax(100px, 1fr) minmax(100px, 1fr);
            gap: 10px;
        }
        .grid-minmax-fr .item { background: #4fc3f7; }

        /* minmax with fixed values */
        .grid-minmax-fixed {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: minmax(50px, 150px) 1fr minmax(50px, 150px);
            gap: 10px;
        }
        .grid-minmax-fixed .item { background: #81c784; }

        /* minmax with auto */
        .grid-minmax-auto {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: minmax(80px, auto) 1fr;
            gap: 10px;
        }
        .grid-minmax-auto .item { background: #ffb74d; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>CSS Grid minmax()</h2>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">minmax(100px, 1fr) x3 - equal columns with 100px minimum</div>
        <div class="grid-minmax-fr">
            <div class="item">Column 1</div>
            <div class="item">Column 2</div>
            <div class="item">Column 3</div>
        </div>
    </div>
