<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Parsing Edge Cases</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 20px;
            font-family: "DejaVu Sans", sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
        }
        h3 { margin: 0 0 15px 0; font-size: 14px; }
        .section { margin-bottom: 15px; }
        .label { font-size: 12px; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 5px; }
        .test-box {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #666;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .expected { font-size: 11px; color: #888; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h3>Phase 6: CSS Parsing Edge Cases (Acid2 Roadmap)</h3>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Invalid property value (should be ignored)</div>
        <style>
            .invalid-value {
                background: yellow;
                width: 200;  /* invalid - no unit */
                height: 50px;
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box invalid-value">width: 200 (no unit)</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: yellow bg, auto width (200 ignored)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Invalid property after valid (valid should apply)</div>
        <style>
            .partial-valid {
                background: lime;
                background: invalid-color;  /* should be ignored, lime stays */
                height: 50px;
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box partial-valid">background: lime then invalid</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: lime background</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Escaped characters in property names</div>
        <style>
            .escaped-prop {
                background: orange;
                height: 50px;
                m\argin: 100px;  /* escaped 'a', should be margin but browsers differ */
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box escaped-prop">m\argin: 100px</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: orange bg (margin behavior varies)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">* html selector (IE6 hack - should not match)</div>
        <style>
            .ie-hack { background: lime; height: 50px; }
            * html .ie-hack { background: red; }  /* should not match in standards mode */
        </style>
        <div class="test-box ie-hack">* html .ie-hack</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: lime (not red)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Invalid !important syntax</div>
        <style>
            .bad-important {
                background: cyan;
                height: 50px;
                border: 5px solid red ! error;  /* invalid, should be ignored */
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box bad-important">border with ! error</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: cyan bg, default border (red ignored)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Multiple values where single expected</div>
        <style>
            .multi-value {
                background: yellow;
                background: red pink;  /* invalid for solid color */
                height: 50px;
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box multi-value">background: red pink</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: yellow (red pink is invalid)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <div class="label">Comment edge case (Acid2 style)</div>
        <style>
            .comment-test {
                background: lime;
                height: 50px;
                /* comment ends here, not at backslash: \*/
                color: white;  /* this should apply */
            }
        </style>
        <div class="test-box comment-test">Comment with backslash</div>
        <div class="expected">Expected: lime bg, white text</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

    <script>
        function toggleTest(el) {
            el.classList.toggle('expanded');
        }

        function filterTests(filter) {
            // Update button states
            document.querySelectorAll('.filters button').forEach(btn => {
                btn.classList.remove('active');
            });
            event.target.classList.add('active');

            // Filter tests
            document.querySelectorAll('.test').forEach(test => {
                const status = test.dataset.status;
                if (filter === 'all') {
                    test.classList.remove('hidden');
                } else if (filter === 'failed' && status === 'passed') {
                    test.classList.add('hidden');
                } else if (filter === 'passed' && status === 'failed') {
                    test.classList.add('hidden');
                } else {
                    test.classList.remove('hidden');
                }
            });
        }

        // Auto-expand failed tests
        document.querySelectorAll('.test[data-status="failed"]').forEach(test => {
            test.classList.add('expanded');
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
